ntromedial pathway gives rise to keratinocytes","Neither pathway contributes to glial cells","Dorsolateral pathway gives rise to enteric neurons","Ventromedial pathway gives rise to melanocytes","Dorsolateral pathway gives rise to melanocytes"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ENeural crest cells follow two main migration pathways during development:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edorsolateral pathway\u003C/strong\u003E, which travels between the dermomyotome and epidermis, gives rise to \u003Cstrong\u003Emelanocytes\u003C/strong\u003E that produce melanin pigment in skin and hair\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eventromedial pathway\u003C/strong\u003E, which travels through the anterior sclerotome, gives rise to multiple cell types including \u003Cstrong\u003Eenteric neurons\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eglial cells\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKeratinocytes\u003C/strong\u003E develop from surface ectoderm, not neural crest cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EGlial cells definitely arise from the ventromedial pathway\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEnteric neurons arise from the ventromedial, not dorsolateral pathway\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EMelanocytes arise from the dorsolateral, not ventromedial pathway\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these migration pathways is crucial as disruptions can lead to various developmental disorders affecting pigmentation and nervous system function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Neural crest cells migrate via dorsolateral and ventromedial pathways during embryonic development","The dorsolateral pathway gives rise to melanocytes which produce melanin in skin and hair","The ventromedial pathway gives rise to neurons, glia, and other cell types including those of the autonomic nervous system"],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Sommer L. Generation of melanocytes from neural crest cells. Pigment Cell Melanoma Res. 2011 Jun;24(3):411-21."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58310"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15938"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58310","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58310"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T09:46:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-22T09:48:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8629"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72840"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4930"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Nervous System","synonyms":[],"desc